    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <head>No. 118.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName>
                            to. Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31</hi>,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Mr. Lowell reports the conclusion arrived at by the British cabinet, which
                        has been put in the form of a memorandum by Lord Granville, as follows:
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The communications which have been made by Mr. Lowell as to the
                                “suspects” in Ireland alleged to be American subjects involve
                                principles of such importance that Her Majesty’s Government consider
                                it better to give their views in a dispatch which I will soon
                                address to Mr. West. In the mean time I may say to Mr. Lowell that
                                the imprisonment of the suspects under the act of last year is not a
                                measure of punishment, but of prevention. * * *]</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
